eviously determined\nbinary inclination of $82.7$ degrees, the implied ejection velocities are as\nhigh as 22000 km s$^{-1}$. These velocities appear unprecedented in nova\noutflows, and are comparable to those seen in supernovae, thereby marking U Sco\nas a truly remarkable object.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Apr 2023 12:51:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 4 May 2023 15:19:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-05"}
